---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, user-scalable=no" />
    <title>EyeMia — Open-Source Eye Gaze Communication System</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="EyeMia is an open-source eye gaze communication system for people with Rett Syndrome, ALS, cerebral palsy, and other conditions that affect motor control."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/fontawesome-all.min.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="no-sidebar is-preload">
    <div id="page-wrapper">

      <!-- Header -->
      <section id="header">

        <!-- Logo -->
        <h1><a href="/hub/">mosaigo</a></h1>

        <!-- Nav -->
        <nav id="nav">
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/hub/">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="/hub/mosoptics/">mosoptics</a></li>
            <li class="current"><a href="/hub/eyemia/">EyeMia</a></li>
            <li>
              <a href="#">Docs</a>
              <ul>
                <li><a href="/getting-started/">Getting Started</a></li>
                <li><a href="/steps/">Step Catalog</a></li>
                <li><a href="/docs-mosoptics/">mosoptics Docs</a></li>
                <li><a href="/docs-eyemia/">EyeMia Docs</a></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/mosaigoio/eyemia">GitHub</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>

        <!-- Banner -->
        <section id="banner">
          <header>
            <h2>Every eye tells a <strong>story</strong></h2>
            <p>
              An open-source eye gaze communication system for people with
              Rett Syndrome, ALS, cerebral palsy, and other conditions that affect motor control.
              Your eyes become your voice.
            </p>
          </header>
        </section>

      </section>

      <!-- Main -->
      <section id="main">
        <div class="container">

          <!-- Hero image -->
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-4 col-12-medium" style="text-align: center;">
              <section class="box">
                <img src="/images/mia1.webp" alt="Mia, the EyeMia mascot" style="max-width: 260px; margin: 0 auto; display: block;" />
                <header>
                  <h3>Meet Mia</h3>
                </header>
                <p>The EyeMia mascot. She sees the world through mosaic-patterned eyes and speaks with her gaze.</p>
              </section>
            </div>
            <div class="col-8 col-12-medium">
              <section class="box">
                <a href="/docs-eyemia/" class="image featured"><img src="/images/portfolio-eyemia.webp" alt="Eye gaze communication board with selection cursor" /></a>
                <header>
                  <h3>Communication is a right, not a luxury</h3>
                </header>
                <p>Rett Syndrome affects about 1 in 10,000 girls, taking away speech and hand use while leaving cognitive ability intact. Eye gaze is their voice. Commercial eye-tracking systems cost $10,000+ and lock families into proprietary ecosystems. EyeMia aims to make eye gaze communication accessible, affordable, and open to everyone.</p>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Who it's for -->
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
              <section>
                <header class="major">
                  <h2>Who it's for</h2>
                </header>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-6 col-12-small">
                    <section class="box">
                      <header>
                        <h3>For Non-Verbal People</h3>
                      </header>
                      <p>Communicate needs, wants, and feelings through eye gaze. Select symbols, words, and phrases by looking at them. Generate speech from selections. Engage with the world through your eyes.</p>
                    </section>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-6 col-12-small">
                    <section class="box">
                      <header>
                        <h3>For Caregivers and Family</h3>
                      </header>
                      <p>Understand what your loved one needs. Configure communication boards, adjust sensitivity, and track usage patterns. A caregiver app gives you control without technical expertise.</p>
                    </section>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-6 col-12-small">
                    <section class="box">
                      <header>
                        <h3>For Teachers and Therapists</h3>
                      </header>
                      <p>Customize symbol grids for learning objectives. Track dwell time patterns to understand attention and progress. Integrate into classroom routines with a dedicated device.</p>
                    </section>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-6 col-12-small">
                    <section class="box">
                      <header>
                        <h3>Open Source and Affordable</h3>
                      </header>
                      <p>No $10,000 proprietary device required. Run on low-power edge hardware with dual USB cameras and a touchscreen. Open source means anyone can improve, adapt, and share it.</p>
                    </section>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Capabilities -->
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
              <section>
                <header class="major">
                  <h2>Capabilities</h2>
                </header>
                <p>A complete eye gaze communication system, from camera to speech, running on affordable edge hardware.</p>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-4 col-6-medium col-12-small">
                    <ul class="default">
                      <li><strong>Real-Time Gaze Tracking</strong> Dual camera gaze detection with precision and jitter smoothing</li>
                      <li><strong>Text-to-Speech</strong> Turn gaze selections into spoken communication</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-4 col-6-medium col-12-small">
                    <ul class="default">
                      <li><strong>Face Recognition</strong> Recognize users to personalize communication boards</li>
                      <li><strong>Head and Movement Tracking</strong> Detect position changes and alert on seizures</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-4 col-6-medium col-12-small">
                    <ul class="default">
                      <li><strong>AI Image Generation</strong> Generate images associated with word meanings for engaging boards</li>
                      <li><strong>Adaptive Calibration</strong> One-time calibration that improves over time</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Status + CTA -->
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
              <section class="box" style="text-align: center;">
                <header>
                  <h2>Project Status</h2>
                  <p>EyeMia is in active early development. The core pipeline framework (mosaigo) and vision library (mosoptics) are being built first. The communication overlay and caretaker app will follow.</p>
                </header>
                <ul class="actions special">
                  <li><a href="/docs-eyemia/" class="button large">Read the Docs</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://github.com/mosaigoio/eyemia" class="button alt large">View on GitHub</a></li>
                </ul>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <section id="footer">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
              <div id="copyright">
                <ul class="links">
                  <li>&copy; 2025-present mosaigoio contributors</li>
                  <li>Apache-2.0 License</li>
                  <li>Part of the <a href="/hub/">mosaigo</a> family</li>
                  <li>Design: <a href="http://html5up.net">HTML5 UP</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Scripts -->
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/jquery.dropotron.min.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/browser.min.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/breakpoints.min.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/util.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/main.js"></script>

  </body>
</html>
